(14, 66, 'Positions Vacant', 'positions-vacant', '<div class="t-content__body formatted">\r\n<h3>Positions available at Avlite Systems</h3>\r\n<strong>Why Avlite?</strong>\r\n<p>A global leader in the design and manufacture of solar-powered aviation lighting systems, Avlite has proven reputation for rapid, innovative and agile technology solutions designed specifically for defense, government, civil and humanitarian aid operations in the most remote toughest environments.</p>\r\nProduct range:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a class="parent" href="../category.php#Airfield-tab" title="Airfield Lighting">Airfield lighting</a></li>\r\n<li><a class="parent" href="../category.php#Obstruction-tab" title="Obstruction Lighting">Obstruction lighting</a></li>\r\n<li><a class="parent" href="../category.php#Heliport-tab" title="Helipad Lighting">Helipad lighting</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Avlite''s products are designed and manufactured in-house using state-of-the-art technology and innovative production processes. Through the efficient design and production of our leading-edge products airports, air services and defence agencies worldwide trust Avlite to enhance the safety of their operations.</p>\r\n<strong>How to apply:</strong>\r\n<p>Unless otherwise stated below, please email your resume and a covering letter (in MS Word format) to <a href="mailto:careers@sealite.com">careers@sealite.com</a> or fax to 03 5977 6124.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div id="jobs_block">\r\n<h1>Systems Engineer</h1>\r\n<p><strong>About the Position:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Systems Engineer reports to the Engineering Manager and responsibilities include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Providing technical sales support, as well as systems and product integration engineering Technical input into tender submissions</li>\r\n<li>System design and product integration, with testing assistance and commissioning of new equipment and installations</li>\r\n<li>Creating technical specifications and test plans</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong> <br />About You:</strong></p>\r\n<p>This role is instrumental across many facets of our business.  Therefore excellent communication skills and the ability to effectively interact with both internal and external stakeholders are paramount.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tertiary qualifications in electrical and/or electronics engineering</li>\r\n<li>Advanced MS Office experience</li>\r\n<li>Ability to read and understand electronic and mechanical documentation</li>\r\n<li>Experience in 2D drafting packages</li>\r\n<li>Industry experience preferable with solar powered systems, marine or aviation navigational aids </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><strong>What we offer in return:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sealite aims to build a culture that celebrates success and strives for industry best practice in everything we do.  We promote a safe, happy and healthy work environment that includes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Annual salary review</li>\r\n<li>Ongoing training and development</li>\r\n<li>Regular social gatherings and end of year party</li>\r\n<li>Free flu shots in winter</li>\r\n<li>Free on-site parking</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Salary will be negotiated with the nominated candidate, based on experience.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>To apply:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please send your resume and covering letter outlining why you should be considered for this role to <a href="mailto:careers@sealite.com">careers@sealite.com</a>. If you are successful in progressing, we will contact you by phone to discuss your application in more detail.</p>\r\n</div>', '', 1, 19, '2013-11-22 02:55:23', 929, '', '2013-11-22 03:16:58', 929, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-11-22 02:55:23', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","